Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease an 8x8 inch baking pan. In a medium-size mixing bowl, blend eggs, sugar, and butter. Mix in matzo meal, cocoa powder and walnuts (if desired). Transfer batter to prepared baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 30 minutes. In a small mixing bowl, blend chocolate, butter or margarine and water. Spread over cooled brownies.